comm: short of a length, just outside off, runs it down to third man to get off the mark right away
Sarfraz is not walking down the wicket to Starc here. Stays in the crease to defend a length ball
he moves back into the crease but the intent is positive. Drives at a length ball, Smith at cover-point makes a diving save

this one swings. Sarfraz, who has walked down to Philander, Steyn etc. so far, is caught with his feet stuck. This one swings a touch back in from outside off. He pushes away from the body. Beaten on the inside edge. Off stump stays safe
bouncer, 150ks already, he ducks it
wide length ball, driven on the up, but straight to Smith at cover-point
outswinger, just outside off, on a length, left alone
good outswing, against the angle, left alone just outside off
short of a length, outside off, opens the face for a single
Sarf walks down this time. Hazlewood digs it in. He has to defend off the back foot
too straight. Sarf is down the wicket again, Hazlewood strays down the pads, and kisses the pad on the way for four leg-byes
short of a length, seams away from just outside off, Sarf wafts at it, and is beaten
lovely delivery. Looks like it will swing back in, pitches just outside off, and then seams away to beat the outside edge
goes for the yorker already, ends up bowling a low full toss at 150ks, the ball runs off the outside half of the bat for one
short of a length, middle and leg, defended to midwicket. 149ks this time
on the pads this time, and Sarfraz is off the mark with a clip fine of long leg
digs this one in short, Sarf goes tall, cuts this to third man for one
nicely played. Shehzad upper-cuts this short ball. Deliberately so, to miss the man at backward point. Not much power behind the shot, just the guiding over the head of the fielder. Gets a couple
walks down the pitch, moves across too, pushes a length ball to third man for one
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
outswinger, on a length, driven, but straight to cover-point
short of a length, outside off, punched away straight to cover. This is bowled at 143ks
bouncer this time, middle and leg, Shehzad ducks it
on a length, good bounce, hits the bat hard. Defended to mid-on
angled across him. Left alone. Called a wide although that doesn't look like one to me
driven on the up. This is a length ball outside off, doesn't swing, and he punches it past cover, to his right
lovely crunchy punch outside off, but straight to cover-point
short of a length, middle and leg, there is no room to swing his arms, but he has somehow short-arm-pulled it past square leg for four. Starc has bowled at 150ks. All that pace has been used here

say what you will of Watson's batting, he is one of the best slip fielders in the world today. This catch is one for the ages. Slip catches are never easy, but the ones that swerve away from you at the last moment? That too to balls bowled at 150.1ks? Sarfraz just follows this quick length ball with his hands, edges it, looks like he has offered an easy catch to Watto until the ball swings away from him at the last moment. Watson has kept his eyes on it throughout, which is why he has dived along with it, facing third man by the time he finishes the catch, diving to the right, taking it with two hands. Almost  ehind his body is the catch completed

what a way to start your innings in the quarter-final. You have just lost out your matchwinner from the two previous matches in the fifth over, your side is notorious for not batting well, what do you do? You walk out and drive the first ball you face on the up, you drive it so hard, it bounces over the fielder at point
bouncer, at 147ks, ducks it

Pakistan openers are back in the sheds already. Plays a loose shot to a wide length ball. Away from the body with no foot movement. The only thing that moves is the ball. Slightly away from him. Takes a thick edge to the second slip where Clarke takes it easily
left alone outside off

the bail doesn't come off, but they are also reviewing the lbw. They are not allowing the review, which is just as well for Australia. This is down the leg side, clips the thigh pad, comes back onto the stumps, clips the leg stump, the bail budges, flashes, but comes back down because it is heavier than usual bails. Clarke looks like he wants to review the lbw because he thinks this has hit the pad normally and not the inside edge of the thigh pad. They run out of time, though, which has saved them a review. But for the thigh pad this is headed well down leg
wide down the leg side
length ball outside off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, good carry, defended off the back foot
length ball, on the pads, worked away for a single
bouncer, 146ks, he ducks it as it is lined outside off
length ball, middle and off, no swing, defended back to him
squares him up a little as Misbah defends a shortish delivery
squared up slightly again as he defends behind square
lovely bouncer at 151.4ks. Misbah sways out of its line, drops his wrists, lets it go through
another bouncer, at 144ks. He sways out of its line again, dropping his wrists
on a length, on off, defended to mid-off
on a length, on off, pushed to mid-off
short of a length, on off, punched to cover
short of a length, middle and off, defended off the back foot
pushed away off the back foot, in front of third man, they come back for two
half-volley, driven hard, but straight to cover
and immediately a false shot. Misbah's mind wants to drive at this full wide ball, but the body hasn't followed. Feet are stuck, the hands don't quite go, but he gets an inside edge to fine leg
full and straight, driven to mid-on
pushed into the leg side for a single
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for one
wide down the leg side
moves across, Johnson angles one across him at 148ks, beats the outside edge as he pushes tentatively
across again, bunts a length ball into the leg side for one
shuffles across again, covers the outswing, defends to cover

this one moves back in exposing the dangers of the movement across. Seams back in from just outside off, but it is bouncing over the stumps. Seems to have rapped him between the unprotected part between the pad and the thigh pad
bouncer, outside off, he ducks it
length ball, angling in, pushed through mid-on, which is unmanned
short of a length, outside off, punched away, but can't beat Warner at backward point
looks to punch this, is cramped for room, hits it straight to cover
short of a length, quick, hits his arm as he fends
short of a length, outside off, right behind it in defence
tucked away off the hip
quick, on a length, pretty straight, defended to leg
bouncer, pretty quick, he ducks it, but this is hostile, and the bounce is a little variable as this one doesn't come up as much as expected. This is bowled at 152.4ks
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
on a length, on off, 143ks, defended back to him
cut away to third man for one
there is no mid-off with this ultra-aggressive field, and he has drilled a full ball through that opening
tucked away off the pads for one
short of a length, into the ribs, nudged away for a single
lovely shot. He opens up the front leg a little, and drives a wide length ball on the up, threading the gap between cover and extra cover
wide length ball, runs this down to third man for one
on a length, on off, right behind it in defence
short of a length, on off, he is right behind it as he defends it to mid-on
looks to steer this to third man but can't beat Warner at backward point
this is called a wide, but Haddin is smiling. This is a mean bouncer, rising from not too short. Damn quick too. Haris wants to pull but can't reach it. This is clocked at 143ks
short of a length, pitched outside leg, worked away into the leg side
length ball, angling in from round the wicket, defended back to him
tossed up outside off, pushed to long-off for one
flighted half-volley, driven to long-off
flat length ball outside off, punched to cover
pushed down to long-off
flighted around off, pushed back to Maxwell

tuk tuk goes bang. Every now and then Misbah plays this shot and invariably he connects. Takes this off a length and sends it over deep midwicket. They need these. Can't let Maxwell sneak in soft overs
short of a length, on off, defended back to him
short of a length, outside off, runs this down to third man
moves across to work this shortish ball off the stumps, takes a second
length ball outside off, defended
on a length, angling in, defends this just outside off
strides forward to defend a length ball
slow offbreak, pushed to cover-point
stays back to punch a length ball to cover-point
down the wicket, not quite to the pitch of the bat, defends this back to him
overpitched, pushed down to long-on for one
short of a length, punched away to extra cover
beats the outside edge as this one doesn't turn back in as expected
on a length, holds its line in front of off, defended
full and straight, almost a half-volley, the mid-on is wide, and he pushes it through that vacant area
short of a length, rising into the chest, Misbah is on his toes as he defends
half-volley outside off, driven down the ground, but straight to mid-off
full, just outside off, slower ball, 129ks, Misbah has read this and defends solidly
swinging back in as he stays full and outside off, draws a thick inside edge that goes for a single to long leg
shortish offbreak, defended off the back foot
short again, stays back this time to pull him to deep midwicket
stays back to a length ball, fails to beat extra cover with the punch
tossed up outside off, pushed straight to extra cover
down the wicket to drive this to long-off for one

and Misbah releases pressure. Moves across early to a full ball, gets a full ball, and slogs it over midwicket for six. It is incredible how often he connects them cleanly but how rarely he attempts them
short of a length, outside off, steered away to third man
length ball outside off, meets it with an open face, gets a single to deep cover
short of a length, on off, stays back to defend
short of a length, pitches leg, angles towards off, defended with an open face

impatience from Sohail. Looks to slog this length ball over midwicket, his head falls back as he plays, gets a big top edge that clears backward point and falls short of third man. Misbah has a word with the youngster
full and straight, worked away for a single to leg
short of a length, on the pads, worked away for one
short of a length, just outside off, defended from the crease
length ball, driven on the up, but back to Faulkner
short of a length, angling in towards off, defended with an open face
wide length ball, opens the face, runs it down to third man for one
short of a length, rising towards the chest, defended with soft hands
drives a length ball uppishly, reaches mid-off on the bounce
that's a sharp short ball, too sharp for him, hits the glove before the bat comes down in the pull shot, but the lob off the glove has cleared Haddin
Sohail might have mis-hit a couple, but he has made us his mind he is not going to get bogged. Clears the front leg to a length ball, and lofts a length ball over mid-on
now gets a shortish ball, runs it down to third man for one
on a length, on off, defended to leg
on a length, on off, defended with an open face
length ball, angling in, worked away to deep midwicket for a single
on a length, on off, no movement, defended to leg
moves right across his stumps, is beaten and hit on the pad, but the ball is pitched outside leg
slower ball, overpitched on middle and leg, pushed to short straight midwicket
digs this one in short, he gets tall, runs this down to third man for one
short of a length, on off, shuffles across to work this to leg for a single
short of a length, seams in a touch, defended from the crease
on a length, in that zone around off, defended from the crease
pushes a length ball to short straight cover
on a length, again in that zone just outside off, defended back to him
slightly wider this time, Misbah pushes it wide of cover for a single
short of a length, on the pads, tucked away square of short fine leg for one
down the wicket to drive this full ball down to long-on

oh will you believe it? Maxwell has brought up the breakthrough. Once again no singles for Misbah have meant Pakistan have to take the risks to keep the runs coming. He has previously hit Maxwell out of the attack with two sixes over midwicket, he tries a third one with a slog-sweep. Not quite to the pitch of the ball this time. Fatal. Top edge sits nicely with Finch at deep midwicket. Strange to see a rare hole-out by Misbah. That too at the short square boundary at Adelaide Oval. The big difference here is he has dragged this from well outside off
down the wicket to drive this to long-off for one
tossed up outside off, gets some drift away, Akmal drives away from the body, gets a thick edge. Would have gone wide of slip even if it had been there
short of a length, turning in, defended to leg
driven to the left of Maxwell who dives and deflects this wide of mid-off for a single
length ball outside off, swings back a touch, hits the inside half of the bat
short of a length, offcutter, moves away from just outside off, beats his outside edge
length ball outside off, allowed to go through to the keeper
bouncer, on off, angling away a touch, he ducks under it
wide half-volley, driven to third man for one
short of a length, rising towards the chest, defended off his toes
goes back to cut a length ball, places it wide of point for a couple
on a length, straight, defended to leg

looks to cut another length ball, but this has come in towards middle and taken the bottom edge, which somehow evades the stumps. Remember what Swann said of cutting offspinners? It's like patting a burning dog
defended to midwicket
worked with the turn, finds square leg

there is an appeal for a hit-wicket, but Akmal is nowhere near the stumps. He has cut this from off, past point, and the bail is off. Haddin, though, has indicated he is not sure and has already gone to the other end even before the replay is shown. It is Haddin's glove that has brought the bail down
worked to leg for one
lovely shot, down the wicket, straight of mid-on
that is a sharp bouncer, on middle and leg, angling towards off. Sohail sways out of its line

the bouncer has done the trick. Johnson has produced the loose drive with leaden feet. Look at his back foot move away as he drives. Johnson pushes this one up, angling it across Sohail, who drives away from the body, his back foot moving away from the line of the ball. The edge is taken
defended off the front foot
low full toss, driven wide of cover
bunted past cover for one
looks to work this to leg but finds midwicket
defends an offbreak to leg
pushed down to long-on for a single
another single to long-on
this one holds its line outside off, or rather doesn't turn as much as expected. Beats the outside edge
short of a length, on off, worked to leg for one
on a length, on off, defended with an open face
full and wide, driven back at Johnson
on a length, outside off, defended off the front foot
driven on the up after moving across to cover the line of the ball. Placed straight of mid-off
slower offcutter, on the pads, worked away

what have you done Umar Akmal? This is a long hop at the Adelaide Oval with short square boundaries. Akmal has enough time to pause, do a quick opinion poll on where to hit this in the stands, and then take a selfie before hitting it. Unfortunately for him, he has found out the one man stationed there. Aaron Finch hasn't had to move an inch. Akmal is disgusted with himself. Smashes the bat into his pad
paddle-sweeps this fine of short fine leg
drives hard at a tossed-up half-volley, slices it over backward point
defended to mid-off
flicked to midwicket
Afridi is down the wicket and drills this length ball straight of long-off for four
length ball, pushed on the up, to long-off

nearly an exceptional return catch. Short of a length, into the ribs, Maqsood looks to fend this to leg, gets a leading edge to his left. This is a soft leading edge, Johnson has enough time to go to his left and take it one-handed. Except that he has to go against the angle. He gets a hand to it, but can't hang on
into the ribs again, at 144.4 ks, defended to leg
full, outside off, pushed to mid-off
tucked away off the hip for a single
wide half-volley, Afridi's bottom hand comes off as he drives. Finds the man at point
short of a length, looks to punch it, gets a thick edge to third man
short of a length, outside off, punched to point
shuffles across to punch this to deep cover for one
deft touch by Afridi after winding up for a big hit. Runs this off the face of the bat over slip for one
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
Maqsood counterattacks. Shuffles across to a length ball, gets under it, and lofts it over mid-on for four
that's No. 351. Oh Shahid, what an entertainer. Length ball, just outside off, he drives with an open face, Finch thinks he is in business at deep point but it sails over it
slower offcutter, Afridi is off pace with this, pushes defensively, is beaten
on a length, outside off, runs this down to third man for one
short of a length, on off, looks to work this to leg, late into the shot and ends up defending this back to Johnson
slower bouncer, Maqsood is early into the shot, is hit in the armpit
short of a length, worked past midwicket for a couple
short ball outside off, Afridi looks to pull this in front of square, is early into the pull and is beaten
looks to run this down to third man from just outside off. Opens the face pretty early. Is beaten
Afridi slashes hard, gets a top edge, and it flies over the keeper's head. This is quite a safe shot. He has given this pull shot his all. More often than not these edges fly safe nowadays
moves across to work a low full toss into the leg side
cut away with both his feet in the air, gets a single to third man

he has found out deep midwicket. Finch has taken three deep midwicket catches today. Oh that short square boundary, what a temptress. Afridi looks to pull, but the ball is not short enough. He doesn't get all of it, Finch is prowling there, and takes this head high. Is this the last time Lala has paced off the field with gloves and pads on?
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
wide length ball, angling away, he throws his bat it, and is beaten by the angle
on a length, outside off, defended to mid-off
yorker outside off, squeezed past backward point
short-arm pull to deep midwicket for one
pushes at a full ball tentatively, is beaten by the angle
short of a length, outside off, punched to mid-off
full ball, driven straight to short cover
slower offcutter, overpitched, driven to mid-on
short of a length, at the stumps, punched back at him
full, on off, driven with an open face, but straight to extra cover
short of a length, punched back at him. Faulkner misfields to allow a single that breaks the maiden
moves across to work a length ball in front of deep midwicket
nearly another wicket for Starc. Short of a length, gets big on Maqsood who tries to flick this to leg. Top edge falls clear of midwicket
yorker, dipping, swinging away, beats the outside edge of the bat
short of a length, on the pads, allows the easy single
driven on the up, the first blemish in the field for Australia as Warner lets it through at backward point
full and outside off, swinging away, beats the push
length ball outside off, driven to deep cover for one
angled across, and he is beaten on the outside edge again. Not quite getting behind the line of the ball
and he beats his bat with an angled full ball again
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point
short of a length, angled across, Wahab tries to open the face for a single. Beaten on the outer edge again
on a length, holds its line around off, defended back to him
full and straight, hit straight to extra cover
bouncer from wide on the crease, beats his attempt at the hook
lovely bowling. Sees him back away and bowls a yorker on the tram line. Oh come on. Marais Erasmus has called this a wide. Cut the bowlers some slack, ump
full outside off, driven to third man for one
wide full ball, swinging away, beats the outside edge

yorker swinging away outside off, past the outside edge. Some appeal from the slips. No touch involved. Starc tells Wahab, "It's the white thing you have to hit." Fair enough. Riaz has missed quite a few. He goes and complains to the umpire. Erasmus shushes the Aussies.
and another yorker. This is straight at the stumps. Outside edge saves him. They get a single to point
and he makes room and swings a length ball through mid-on for four
swings and misses here
sees him give the charge and bounces him at 141ks. Riaz is swaying out of the line hoping it doesn't hit him
short of a length, at the chest, fended away for one. A silly shy at the stumps from Johnson, and they concede four extra runs
slower ball, legcutter, driven down the ground
full, on off, driven hard straight to mid-off
Wahab gets a touch on that little white thing, the low full toss, gets an edge to the keeper. On the bounce
that little white thing has gone to the wide long-on boundary. Wahab makes room, Starc follows him with a full ball, Riaz whips it without a back lift, clears midwicket
bouncer at 150ks. Good response from Starc. Riaz gets under the ball
yorker outside off, dug out for a single
moves across to push a low full toss straight to mid-on
short of a length, angling in, pushed into the off side for a single
short of a length, on off, punched to mid-off
looks for the sweep from outside off, looking to go square, gets a thick inside edge onto the pad

good shot but he had found the fielder. Full ball, on off, he knows there is no deep cover, he is looking to drive over the ring, just gets too close to the pitch of the ball, and finds Johnson at cover
short of a length, just outside off, beats the outside edge
full, just outside off, pushed to point with an open face
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
he is full and outside off, and he beats the bat again as this holds its line against the angle

Starc is the sole leading wicket-taker this World Cup. Finally he has drawn an edge. Riaz has finally hit that little white thing after backing away from the stumps. The outside edge settles nicely with Haddin
full, angling in, he gets the bat down in time, and gets a couple wide of midwicket. Just in time the bat comes down
bouncer, angling in, this time he ducks under it
yorker outside off, squeezes under the bat
length ball, angling in, nicely guided past midwicket
length ball outside off, moves across to defend
short of a length, just outside off, defended from the crease
full, swinging in, worked to long leg. Good running brings them the second
short of a length, angling in, defended to leg
full, swinging in, too straight, goes for a leg-bye

Hazlewood ends with four in the quarter-final. Sohail backs away and swings. Gets a massive top edge that goes a million miles and comes down towards gully. Haddin the man with mitts on clears the area, settles under it, keeps his eyes on the swirling ball, and takes a safe catch
yorker, on off, Rahat keeps it out
bouncer, angling in, he ducks under it
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
full toss outside off, swinging away, beats the outside edge
full, angling in to off, he stays back and brings the bat down. The outside edge rolls wide of third slip

falls short of what could have been the 19th wicket for Starc. Now he will have to wait for SCG. This is full and straight, he stays back, is squared up, edges it softly, and it falls short of the diving second slip
short of a length, angling away, beats the outside edge
short of a length, angling away, beats the cut this time
slower legcutter, runs off the thick outside edge for a single to point
short of a length, on off, defended to leg
short of a length, tucked away off the hip with soft hands, gets a couple
full outside off, played with open face to deep point for a single
length ball outside off, defended with an open face
length ball outside off, bunted for a single to point
on a length, pretty straight, defended to mid-off
Watson slips in a sharp bouncer. Adil manages to keep the pull shot down for a single
full, angling in, pushed to mid-on
short of a length, seaming in, cramps him up for room. Defended
full, outside off, pushed to mid-off
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
on a length, outside off, gets a single to mid-off
short of a length, on off, makes room to slash, and is beaten
on a length, no room, gets a thick leading edge towards cover
he makes room and swings, gets a thick edge that clears the cover ring
bouncer, he makes room and tries to pull. Beaten by the height of it
another bouncer, and beats the top edge once again as he backs away
short again, hurries onto him, the pull ends up going to cover. Doesn't carry
full and straight this time, there is no room, Rahat keeps it out
short of a length, makes room to swing into the leg side, and is beaten by the angle that cramps him up
looks for the yorker, which swings in, but concedes a single off the inside edge
makes room to try to slog one to leg, gets a bottom edge for a single
that had come out of nowhere. First boundary in exactly nine overs. Faulkner bowls length with mid-on up, and he clears the front leg to clear that man
tries the same shot this time but Faulkner slips in a bouncer to beat him
moves all over the crease before coming back to his normal stance, and edges this back over the bowler's head for a couple

this time it has gone to hand. Faulkner gets a wicket, Starc takes a lovely catch. Clears the front let to pull, gets a top edge towards top edge, Starc rushes in and takes this low and diving forward
starts over the wicket, pitched up and shaping a touch on off stump, Warner leans into a punchy drive, straight to extra cover
full length again, swinging back a touch and Warner chops the ball on to his front pad, little loose but he gets away with it

lovely timing, just a tickle coming forwards, basically Warner has defended this on the up and beat the fielder, who only had a yard or two to move, it races to the boundary for the first four of the innings
Sohail is pitching the ball up, looking for any movement on offer, Warner is quick to tuck in again, gets this straight back past the bowler but mid-on gives chase

first ball to Finch, nip-backer from Sohail and he's interested, the ball loops to slip but there was not bat involved... Dharmasena gives a serene shake of the head and Misbah decides not to gamble. Looked a little high, Hawk-Eye says it would have just clipped the top of off
length ball around the line of off, Finch taps it defensively into the covers
touch straight to begin with, length ball pinged off the pads by the effervescent Warner, gets a couple through midwicket
pushes this wider, angling away from the left-hander, plinks it off the toe of the bat towards point
slashed but slashed hard, Warner's railway sleeper of a bat gets a chunk of the ball, flies over the head of second slip and away
fullish, around the line of off, comes forward and blocks into the covers
full and wide of the stumps, Warner frees the arms menacingly and hammers the ball along the ground to extra cover
length ball on middle and off, Warner stays back and whips it to the on side, picks out mid-on this time
length ball in the channel outside off, Finch shuffles across, punches it on the up and picks a gap in the covers
decent line, comes forward and blocks to the off side

pitched up, this jags back at Finch and raps him on the pads, Sohail implores for the decision... and Dharmasena gives it! Finch, after a brief conversation with his partner, asks for the review but it only takes a quick look to release this was foolishness. Not much footwork and the ball zipped in with the arm, past the inside edge as he played to leg, and it was crashing into the woodwork halfway up. The finger points skywards for a second time and Pakistan celebrate to the heavens
touch shorter to begin with, outside off stump, Smith gets across to defend
pitched up a little more, coming back into the right-hander, Smith closes the face and nudges to midwicket
length ball around the line of off, gets across and shows it a solid straight bat in defence
stays back and pushes defensively into the off side
length delviery, pushed across, Warner covers up in front of off stump
angled across in the channel outside off, Warner cocks the triggers but mishits into the covers
offered width again, tries to crash it through the off side but again fails to connect properly
punched off the back foot, that's out of the meat, nicely played in front of backward point and he gets a couple
pitched up, inviting the drive and Warner is a man that doesn't need much invitation, slaps it straight to Umar Akmal who fields it cool as you like in the covers
pitched up and tailing in on the stumps, a la Finch's dismissal, Smith plays those in his sleep, though, flicking a leg glance through square for four
length and in the corridor, nibbles away from the batsman, who is happy to leave
gets across in front of off stump and pushes the ball back towards mid-on
good length, well outside off but Smith still turns it to leg, works it wide of mid-on for a single
Sohail fires this across Warner's bows, chops it into the ground and it bobbles towards cover
slightly back of a length, on the stumps, swivels the hips and flicks one through midwicket
starts with a gentle half-tracker and Warner crunches it high over the covers and away for four. Er, we'll call that a loosener
still a touch short and this one veering towards leg, nudged off the hips for a single
continues over the wicket to Smith, back of a length and defended from the crease
too full, Rahat gives up another four ball, in the channel and Smith shows he can play the cover drive too, stroke it through the infield and away
better length, outside off, brings down a straight bat and pushes to mid-off
walks to the off side, Rahat pitches full on middle and is whipped away for three more, Smith likes it there, wristy nudge through midwicket
touch full and well outside off, making sure Smith can't get it off his pads, left alone
similar line, gets on to the front foot and taps defensively into the covers
short ball from Sohail, doesn't get up quite as Smith is expecting, bottom edges a pull down on the pitch
shot! Full outside off, just a half-step into the ball and then the wrists come through, cracks four through extra cover. Another boundary for Smith, who's made a smooth start
shortens his length, straighter line and Smith gets out his big spoon, happily nurdles away to the leg side
length ball outside off, Warner dabs into the off side from the crease
good pace from Rahat, up above 140pkh, Smith uses that to work the ball through square for a couple
goes back and across and defends down the track
fullish, in the channel, gets on the front foot and defends
slightly back of a length, pushed across from over the wicket, Smith hops back and chops the ball towards mid-off
length delivery, decent line around off stump, Smith steers the ball in front of square
nicely played, back-foot punch and he gets the ball between extra cover and mid-off, Misbah gives chase but Smith gets a comfortable two
over the wicket, shortish and a little wide, Warner latches on to it but his cut doesn't quite connect, still nearly runs all the way
back of a length at the body, nudged behind square
wild, down the leg side and Warner whirls his arms at a pull in vain

banged in, short and wide... and Warner has flubbed it straight to third man! Wahab strikes, his 15th wicket of the tournament to go joint third. Warner has gifted him this one, though, was trying to use the pace but really just hung the bat out and steered an uppercut to the fielder, decent low catch from Rahat who ran in a good way
short and angled across, Wahab's hitting 145kph already, left alone
straighter line, Clarke shuffles across and clips a couple firmly through midwicket to get going
slightly back of a length, in the channel, Clarke hangs back and steers a single to third man
bangs this in halfway down, doesn't get up that much and Clarke defends softly on to the pitch
on the stumps and a touch short, works this away through square
continues to drop short, 140kph and over middle and off, Clarke squares up and defends back to the bowler
goes fuller now, around the line of off, shows it the maker's name in defence
pitched up around middle and off, Clarke punches along the ground to mid-on
bit of width, pushed across on a length, hangs back and swats a couple wide of third man
shortish and pulled into the ground through square

back of a length and this gets big on Clarke, who gets on top of it, drops the ball behind backward point and calls for the run, Smith has to get motoring but Ahmed Shahzad's throw misses. Would have been in anyway
banged in at the body, Smith paddles it around the corner for one more

gottim! The short ball works, Clarke dollies it to forward short leg! Don't you love it when a plan comes together... That was well-directed from Wahab, not quite a snorter but awkward enough for a man with an antique spine, rising towards the helmet grill and Clarke can only pop it up off the splice, floats into the hands of the catcher. Maqsood hurls the ball at the floor and screams in delight. Pakistan are in this
slams the ball in short and Watson has to take evasive action, fiery stuff
length this time, 150kph and Watson shapes to play and then raises the bat out of the way... Wahab glares at him for one, two, three seconds, then starts loudly applauding his team-mates
slanted across the right-hander from over the wicket, shaping away off a length and no stroke offered
goes across and works a length ball through the leg side
length ball and this seams a touch as Watson hangs back, wanted to turn to leg but skips off the edge through gully
lovely stuff from Smiffy, calm as you like, waits for the slightly full delivery and then caresses it through the covers, too much gas for Misbah in the end
good length, drops back and pushes into the off side
Rahat has a FSL in now as well, Smith teases him by working a bouncer down and away behind square
steams in, short and rising, worked away through square off the back foot
dug in, spits at Watson, he limbos away, jerking his head at the last minute... Wahab is bringing the heat, as advertised
short again, this time a touch leg side and Watson flinches almost involuntarily... Dharmasena doesn't call wide, either
back of a length, 150kph/93mph and blocked solidly off the back foot
on the stumps, fast and accurate, again Watson defends
a ripper, so close to the glove! Just a fraction short and skidding on at a horrible angle, Watson spasms in the crease but just manages to drop his hands out of the way. Terrific stuff from Wahab
floated up outside off stump, Smith prods into the covers
the googly this time, not sure Smith picked it, an inside edge squirts behind square on the leg side
a touch short - not what you want to see if you're standing where Misbah is - topsinner from Afridi and Watson rocks back to pull one to deep midwicket
length outside off, skids on and driven through the covers to the sweeper
floated up a bit further, drifting towards middle and leg, Smith whips one to long-on
tossed up and Watson pushes back on the off side from the crease
shortish and stabbed away, Maqsood reacts well at short leg to move to his right and cut the ball off
length outside off, still hitting 150kph after the break, blocked into the off side
short and pulled into the ground down through backward square

god golly, that's a helluva ball, Watson does well to keep it down and away from the catcher on the leg side, climbing from just back of a length and thudding into the splice as the batsman threw his hands up
banged in again and this loops towards short leg, won't quite carry! The barrage from Wahab is unrelenting, again had Watson hopping around like a man on coals
short and rising to catch the shoulder of the bat, this flies over the cordon but short of the third man! Serious working over for Watson but he survies
pushed through around off stump, tapped back towards mid-off
walks out and punches a single along the ground to long-on
floated up around the line of off and clipped for four, quick hands from Smith and not afraid to hit against the turn, no one out at deep midwicket and that is a welcome boundary
works this past midwicket again but long-on has moved around and prevents another four
tossed up and punched into the covers
full and on the stumps, again Smith closes the face to send the ball scuttling into a gap square on the leg side

bounced him out, Wahab's plan works a treat... except for Rahat dropping the ball! Oh dear, oh dear, Rahat, what have you done? Straight down the throat of fine leg, Watson never in control of a wild hook but the fielder butchers it. Wahab bellows in frustration, could be a huge moment
angled across, length ball blocked from the crease
shortish outside off, Smith defends down the track to the bowler... and Wahab throws down the stumps in frustration
charges in once again, hits the deck hard and Smith deals with a rising ball around his ribcage, works one through square
vicious lifter from Wahab, ever-so-slightly leg side and Watson gets his equipment out of the way... signalled wide and that's means an extra ball for Watto to survive
close again! Watson is being peppered, again takes his eyes off it, hits high up the bat as he fends away the offending delivery, short of the catcher
pitches this up, aiming for leg-before, Watson has steeled himself and works a couple off his pads
length ball on the stumps, tapped short on the leg side
slightly short, hangs back and punches to the right of extra cover, takes the pace off it but can't prevent a run
half-tracker from Sohail, following Wahab's lead but without the venom, Watson rolls his wrists and clatters four in front of deep square leg
touch short but in the channel outside off, played into the covers
that's a better bouncer, climbing above shoulder height as it whirs back at Watson, only 137kph but beats the attempted pull
banged in even shorter, all height and no trousers, really, and Watson swerves under it
back of a length, 147kph and Smith gets in line, turns behind square
another grumpy bumper from furious Wahab, hits the splice as Watson clings on to his batting existence
slammed in short, very short and called wide as it sails over the batsman...
lets this go a little early, maybe attempting to trap Watson on the crease with a yorker, bunts the full toss back along the ground
short and wanged down the leg side, Wahab losing his line a touch, maybe flagging
dug in at the body, this time Watson gets on top of it and turns the ball down behind square for runs
straight, on a length, gets half forwards and nudges to the leg side
shortish and Watson takes it on the thigh pad, back in the crease... Some of the fire has been doused, could be Wahab's last
good length, Smith comes forward to block
back and across and nudges one through square leg
touch too full from Sohail, in the slot for Watson to cream a drive, all his Wahab troubles forgotten, beats the despairing dive from Misbah and runs away to the cover boundary
full length and tailing towards the pads, Watto clips a couple more through midwicket
off stump, goodish length, Watson plants the front foot and defends
pitched up on the stumps, hasn't got the pace to discomfit the batsman, glanced behind square
length outside off, Watson mistimes a chop into the covers
comes forward and punches the ball towards mid-off on the up
angled across, slightly back of a length and steered through point for a single
sliding across the batsman, looked just about inside the tramlines... but called wide as Smith ignores it
pitched up in the channel, Smith strokes another boundary, pinged through extra cover giving the man in the deep no chance... Raise of the bat for fifty, been a silky knock
touch short, around off stump, jabbed back towards the bowler
pushed towards the slips and Smith taps into the off side coming forwards
short and sitting up outside off, Watson bullies this away for four, front-foot pull and it goes off the bat with a crack through midwicket
Sohail gives up some more loose change, boinging this halfway down and way over the batsman's head
well, this is daft... he's not going to get out if he can't hit them. Pakistan have got carried away with Wahab's success against Watson and Sohail slams another one in that rises too high
better length, still short and climbing towards the throat, defended on the back foot
short ball, skidding through the body but made to look like a long hop by Watson, wheels a pull away and beats fine leg, four more
length outside off and pushed back to mid-off
now that's a bit smarter, slips in the yorker and Watson nearly overbalances, digs it out to midwicket
slightly short, outside off, plays through the line and picks up one through the covers
floated up outside off from around the wicket, drilled to long-off
drops a little short, wide of the stumps and cut off the back foot through point
short again, Watson hangs back and clatters it to extra cover
gives this some air, floated towards off stump, leans out to defend
some turn? Flighted from Sohail, around off stump and straightens to clips the edge as Watson pushes forwards, runs behind square
tossed up and drifting to leg, Smith flicks at it, runs off the pad, I think, to short fine leg
drops a little short, Watson pulls through midwicket
pushed through on middle and leg, clipped square for a single
sliding on with the arm towards leg stump, guided away off the pads behind square
short from Afridi, not got that zip off the surface as yet, Watson crunches a meaty pull down the ground, cut off at long-on
flighted, comes forward, taps one more through mid-on
tossed up, googly on leg stump, worked with the turn (such as it is) to deep square leg
tossed up, played back to the bowler coming forwards
length ball, straightening a fraction outside off, punched down the ground to long-off
floated up on the stumps, Smith dinks one more back past the bowler
very full, gets forward and boshes another single to long-on
flighted, gets Smith reaching around his front pad, pushed back to the bowler a little uncertainly
flatter and swatted away through the covers for the fourth single from the over
angled in with the arm, can't get this one away
skidding on and pushed back
flat on middle stump, Smith gets to the pitch of it anyway and clubs towards long-on, which is vacant, bounces just before the rope
touch short on the stumps, trapped to leg from the crease
flighted outside off, leans out and steers a couple more through the covers
tossed up, luring Smith out and then it dips on him, done in the flight but he manages to thrust his hands out and prevent it slipping past
slightly short of a length, popped into the leg side, aerial shot from Smith but into a gap
slightly short again, outside off, chopped to backward point where Shahzad makes a smart diving stop but can't prevent one
back of a length, around off stump, blocked

fuller, on the stumps, Smith flicks and misses - given! Adil's appeal was almost a lone one, though Sarfraz also went up, Dharmasena gave it some thought before raising the finger. Australia have used their review, so Smith has to trudge off, having looked impenetrable for the last couple of hours. Looked like it would have clipped leg, fairly innocuous ball, Smith not quite as focused as he had been
length on off stump, Maxwell is busy already, pushes at it, opens the face and runs one to third man to get off and running
parsimonious length on off stump, Watson guards his wicket like a sentry
decent line to begin with, Maxwell avoids getting funky, dabs into the covers
goodish length around off stump, prodded carefully back on the off side
pitched up outside off, nice and juicy and Maxwell throws the bat, think the toe hit the ground, there was a sound as it zipped through but Erasmus wasn't interested
length ball around off, 140kph and a tight line, pushed away defensively this time
straighter and hit on the pads, caught him on the move but probably a little high
super shot, timed the pants off that, touch full from Rahat and Maxwell stroked it back past mid-off, first boundary for him
charges in, Watto can see the whites of his eyes from 22 yards away, back of a length and jabbed into the covers

banged in, Maxwell flaps at it, massive miscue, halfway between a ramp and a top-edged saucapan swat, flies way up, down towards third man - but Sohail Khan drops it on the run! Barely gets a hand on it before stumbling over, Wahab screams in anguish for the second time tonight
more chin music, Maxwell decides not to take this one
length ball, fired down the leg side, Maxwell swings at it anyway
rising off a length, shuffles back and across, pushed into the covers for one
length ball on the stumps, clipped of the pads past square leg
shortish, worked off the body into the leg side
back of a length, cramps Maxwell as he tries to force of the back foot, a whisker away from his outside edge
outside off, length this time, pushed into the off side
length ball in the channel, driven on the up to the man at cover
this is just a smidge short but Maxwell contorts himself and manufactures a shovelled-pull through midwicket, in the air but no one there and he gets fours
length outside off, Maxwell reaches for the drive, hits high up the bat but falls short of short extra cover and deflects for one
touch full, in the corridor but Watson is far from uncertain, plants his tree trunk and belabours a cover drive to the boundary
pitched up on leg stump, not quite the yorker and Maxwell times it supremely off his toes for four through mdiwicket
steps to leg, Wahab follows him, drops short and Maxwell somehow blaps it through backward point, sort of a tennis shot, totally off balance and yet is whistles away
bangs this in short, rolls the wrists on a pull, gloves behind square for one
drops back outside off and guides a single off an open bat face
bouncer from Wahab, Maxwell tries to chop down the beanstalk, fails to connect
back of a length again, very leg side... Wahab tiring, I think
goes full and outside the line of off, Maxwell stays still and drills a couple more out to deep extra cover
slower ball from Adil, dips on Watson but he's waiting, slaps it to midwicket and jogs through to complete his half-century
slightly full outside off, Maxwell's arms were born free but he carves the ball to cover
pitched up and defended on the front foot, into the ground and Adil leaps to get a hand on it
fullish and straight, dances across and pings the ball to mid-on
dismissive from Maxwell, little bit of width and he crunches the ball on the up, sails in front of extra cover and away for four
short ball, Maxwell takes the bait, there's a man out there... but he'd need to be in the crowd. Effortless swivel-pulled six to finish the over and kick Pakistan in the bojangles once more
shortish, stays back and blocks to the leg side
there is it, the symbol of victory, Watson takes on the Wahab bouncer and this time nails it into the crowd, over the head of deep square leg. No coming back from here
good length on off stump and Watson defends this, almost theatrically, back to the bowler
veers leg side, back of a length and tickled fine, wide of the keeper and that will run away. Coming in a flood now, Pakistan's World Cup ebbing away
dug in short, outside off stump, Watson gets on top of it and defends to the off side

rapid bumper to finish, Watson ducks the challenge and then gets mouthful of filth from Wahab, who came all the way down to congratulate Australia on their semi-final place pass on his thoughts. Watson chuckles like a baby with a rattle
full and homing on middle and leg stump, glanced fine for a couple
outrageous. But since it's Maxwell, maybe just run of the mill... Full outside off, Maxwell crouches and scoop-slaps the ball into the stands at deep backward point
slower ball on leg stump, spots it and deflects on behind square
pitched up in the channel, driven into the ground, over the bowler's head, Watson sends Maxwell back as mid-off fields

fullish length outside off, driven into a gap, the field is up, Watson raises his arms in celebration... Australia have won by six wickets and will take their place in the last four. It was only briefly in doubt when Wahab Riaz was putting a hex on Watson but two dropped catches off his bowling snuffed out Pakistan's faint hopes
